    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe 'wrap' option is not respected in :terminal mode. \n\nThe terminal output wraps around to the next line if the lines are longer than the current window instead of continuing out of view to the right.\n\n:h terminal-config says that 'wrap' is disabled but the option doesn't seem to effect the behaviour of this. \n\nThis also has the negative effect of inserting newlines in terminal output which are present when copying the terminal output.\n\nIs this a limitation of the terminal emulator I use or :terminal? This is present on both gnome-terminal and st terminal emulators from what I can tell.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nClone the latest master branch:\n```sh\ngit clone --depth 1 https://github.com/neovim/neovim\nmake CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -C neovim\n./neovim/build/bin/nvim --clean +terminal\n```\nConfirm 'wrap' is set to 'nowrap':\n```vim\nset wrap?\n```\nPrint a long line in the :terminal window:\n```sh\nprintf 'A%.0s' {1..1000}\n```\nSee the long line getting wrapped multiple times:\n```\nAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA\nAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA\nAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA\nAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA\nAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA\nAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA%                                           \n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe behaviour I expect is that the printf's single line output not wrap multiple lines but instead keep printing on the same line off to the right and out of view.\n\nThis would be the same behaviour as 'nowrap' in regular files, allowing the user to pan to the right with motions like zL and zH or anything in :h scroll-horizontal.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-a5e5ec8 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1767980792\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 9.1.285\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.12\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst 0.9.2 and gnome-terminal 3.58.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color and xterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuilt from source",
